==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[bien pensant#French|bien pensant]], literally ‘well thinking’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/bjɛ̃ pɑ̃sɑ̃/}}

===Adjective===
'''[[bien]] [[pensant]]'''
# right-thinking, [[orthodox]], conformist

===Noun===
'''[[bien]] [[pensant]]'''
# a person who is ''bien pensant'', a conservative

